author: news.com.au
title: dollar lower ahead of key economic data
text:
Video Image CommSec: AM report 2 October 1:57 US sharemarkets were mixed ahead of the release of key employment data. Shares in Twitter fell 8.4 percent with some analysts saying this was in response to reports that co-founder Jack Dorsey would be named the permanent Chief Executive.
October 2nd 2015 19 days ago /video/video.news.com.au/Business/ The ABS will release retail spending figures for August today.
AAP Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google+ Share on Reddit Email a friend THE Australian dollar is lower ahead of the release of local retail spending figures and US employment data. At 0630 AEST on Friday, the local unit was trading at 70.30 US cents, down from 70.64 cents on Thursday.
On Friday the Australian Bureau of Statistics will release retail spending figures for August and the market is expecting a 0.4 per cent rise, after a 0.l per cent fall the previous month.
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON FRIDAY
One Australian dollar buys:
* 70.30 US cents, from 70.64 cents on Thursday
* 84.31 Japanese yen, from 84.86 yen
* 62.87 euro cents, from 63.39 euro cents
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session)
Source: IRESS
